      "writtenOn": "2020-06-26T14:18:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The thread safety issue here isn\u0027t limited to flushAndSubmit being called on one thread at a time.\n\n1) It must be called on a specific thread for OpenGL.\n\n2) No other thread can be doing anything else with the GrContext or its owned objects.\n\nWe might just need a different cache strategy here. I believe the old model was that flushing would free things up because you could flush anything that was previously recorded. Now with DDL recorders we need the client to explicitly draw the DDL to the direct context before anything from that recorder becomes purgeable (AIUI). So if you have multiple recorders adding stuff to this cache they can\u0027t actually free each others\u0027 entries. Maybe we just let this grow unbounded on the recording side and the direct context frees as much as it can when DDLs are drawn to get as close to being under budget as possible. We\u0027d only guarantee that we\u0027re under budget when all DDLs have been flushed (and we\u0027re not recording new ones).",
      "parentUuid": "0667d166_6230c225",
      "revId": "908b2bdfd68abe37c5e798c34d43080bb38ec5aa",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
